I see the issue. The error `"Could not find the table 'public.habit_configs' in the schema cache"` usually means one of two things:
1.  The table doesn't exist yet (you haven't run the migration).
2.  The table exists, but Supabase's API layer (PostgREST) hasn't refreshed its cache to "see" the new table.

I have updated the migration script to include a command that forces this cache refresh. I have also updated the database service to handle this specific error code (`PGRST200`) more gracefully as a warning, so it falls back to local storage instead of crashing or spamming errors.

